Description: Fragment of oval handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Production date: 143 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Name Anaxandros. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 163, 6 (if Petrie erred)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1074)
